In this statement, the President addresses the issue of obstruction in Congress and expresses his satisfaction with a bipartisan group of Senators taking action to fix the problem. He emphasizes that a single Senator or a few Senators should not be able to block or delay legislation for political reasons. The President mentions the importance of making critical decisions on various issues such as gun violence prevention, immigration reform, fiscal responsibility, and job creation, and states that unnecessary obstruction cannot be afforded. The President also expresses gratitude to Congress for changing Senate rules to consider district court judicial nominations more routinely. He highlights the long delays faced by his judicial nominees and urges the Senate to treat all of his nominees fairly. The President sees these reforms as a positive step towards a more efficient system.